<h4 class='text-dark'>FAQ: 3. Why is it beneficial to shift the pattern of failures in reliability centered maintenance (RCM)?</h4>
<p class='text-muted'><strong>Answer:</strong> - Shifting the pattern of failures, such as from random to age-related wear, can make it easier to predict and manage maintenance activities. By focusing on reducing random or infant mortality failures and promoting age-related wear, organizations can improve the reliability and efficiency of their maintenance practices.</p>
